body:
i'm going to guess it may be fixed with this #2474 

can you check @davidak?

i don't know how. you can try to reproduce it on a test-server (you may have lots of them).

i have shared 2 folders with a group called "alle" with all accounts (2, including myself). it can be that it creates an infinity loop...

okay, i have cloned the master of core, copied /config and /data, chown www-data and opened it in chrome... 500

```
root@owncloud-performance-test:/var/www/owncloud# php index.php
php fatal error:  require_once(): failed opening required 'phpass/passwordhash.php' (include_path='/var/www/owncloud/lib:/var/www/owncloud/config:/var/www/owncloud/3rdparty:/var/www/owncloud/apps:/var/www/owncloud/lib:.:/usr/share/php:/usr/share/pear:/var/www/owncloud') in /var/www/owncloud/lib/user/database.php on line 36
```

or should i clone stable5?

i have done that.

```
root@owncloud-performance-test:/var/www/owncloud# php index.php
php fatal error:  require_once(): failed opening required 'phpass/passwordhash.php' (include_path='/var/www/owncloud/lib:/var/www/owncloud/config:/var/www/owncloud/3rdparty:/var/www/owncloud/apps:/var/www/owncloud/lib:.:/usr/share/php:/usr/share/pear:/var/www/owncloud') in /var/www/owncloud/lib/user/database.php on line 36
```

same error
@davidak you need master for 3rdparty as well
is everything resolved now? what's the new log for?

this seems to fix the individual file deletion only when using non-shared folders. if you try to upload or delete a file within a shared folder, the problem persists with all the same symptoms as @davidak .

update: after completing the process correctly, i can confirm that this bug has been fixed.

same error : php fatal error:  require_once(): failed opening required 'phpass/passwordhash.php' 
what can i do ?? thanks

solved with this : 
rm -rf owncloud/3rdparty
http://owncloud.org/contribute/ (i followed this tutorial, and then 3rdparty was in double) next to owncloud directory and inside owncloud directory...
seems everything's good with all 3 commenters. if not, add a comment.
